    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9804" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ὠρί̄ων</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">Orīon</span>,
          the mighty hunter, beloved of Eos, <i><span class="en">Od.
            5.121</span></i>. Slain by Artemis, he continues to follow the chase in
          the nether world, <i><span class="en">Od. 11.572</span></i>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">310</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            18.486</span></i>. He appears even in Homer as a constellation, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.488</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            5.274</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
